{
  "competency_question": "Identify the substrate that accumulates in Fabry disease and explain why",
  "answer_summary": "Globotriaosylceramide (Gb3/GL-3) accumulates in Fabry disease due to deficiency of alpha-galactosidase A (GLA), the lysosomal enzyme that catalyzes hydrolysis of Gb3. GLA is encoded by the GLA gene on Xq22.1. When GLA activity is absent or reduced (due to pathogenic GLA variants), Gb3 cannot be degraded and progressively accumulates in lysosomes throughout the body, particularly in vascular endothelium, kidney, heart, and nervous system.",
